ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Started school or a training program after not going to school for a long time
3. Graduated from school or training program
4. Had problems in school or in training program
6. Did not graduate from school or training program
7. Became involved in a romantic relationship
9. Became pregnant if female/girlfriend became pregnant if male
11. Birth of a second or later child
17. New person moved into the household
18. Person moved out of the household
19. Someone stayed on in the household after he/she was expected to leave
21. A change in the frequency of family get-togethers
26. Moved to a better residence or neighborhood
27. Moved to a worse residence or neighborhood
28. Moved to a residence or neighborhood no better or worse than the last one
29. Unable to move after expecting to be able to move
30. Lost a home through fire, flood, or other disasters
33. Were in an accident in which there were no injuries
34. Were involved in a law suit
35. Were accused of something for which a person could be sent to jail
39. Got involved in a court case
43. Didn't get out of jail when expected
44. Increased involvement in church or synagogue, club, neighborhood, or other organization
46. Were not able to take a planned vacation
47. Took up a new hobby, sport, craft, or recreational activity
50. Had a frightening experience with drugs or alcohol
53. Were the subject of a cruel rumor
54. Were excluded from a peer group
